    headline.innerHTML = "Wow! A new headline!";
};
</pre><br><h2> event handling - method 1<div style="font-size: 0.5em; color: blue;"><a class="dcTOCTop" title="Go to top of tiddler" href="javascript:;"> [top]</a></div></h2><br><h2> event handling - method 2<div style="font-size: 0.5em; color: blue;"><a class="dcTOCTop" title="Go to top of tiddler" href="javascript:;"> [top]</a></div></h2><br><h2> event handling - method 3<div style="font-size: 0.5em; color: blue;"><a class="dcTOCTop" title="Go to top of tiddler" href="javascript:;"> [top]</a></div></h2><br><br><h1> File IO <div style="font-size: 0.5em; color: blue;"><a class="dcTOCTop" title="Go to top of tiddler" href="javascript:;"> [top]</a></div></h1>read, write, streams <br><br><h1> Debugging <div style="font-size: 0.5em; color: blue;"><a class="dcTOCTop" title="Go to top of tiddler" href="javascript:;"> [top]</a></div></h1>syntax errors, logic errors<br>text editor color coding <br>wrong math<br>reproduce the problem<br>firebug <br><br><h1> Object Orientation <div style="font-size: 0.5em; color: blue;"><a class="dcTOCTop" title="Go to top of tiddler" href="javascript:;"> [top]</a></div></h1>class - the blueprint, representation of groups attributes/properties (data/variables) or behavior/methods (functions)<br>object - is the thing itself, can create multiple objects based on one class<br>encapsulation - box them up (both properties and methods)<br><pre>objects - they are smart, they have methods and properties 
    array
    variable
